What to do when your kids don’t like cake! Here’s a fun way to make their ice cream cones a little more festive. And it’s super easy! 🎉

Melt chocolate chips in a bowl in the microwave in 20-30 second increments stirring in between until melted. Dip the edge of the cone into the chocolate and use the side of the bowl to smooth it out. Then dip into sprinkles. Set upright until cooled. Add your favorite ice cream and celebrate 🎊

Sharing one of my og recipes from my blog just in time for Cinco de Mayo! This Fresh Lime Margarita is the perfect not too sweet and not too tarte marg. And in my opinion you should always have it with salt on the rim! I’d love to hear if you are going to make it, have made it before or say hi if you have had one at my house with me 🤣 cheers! 

Cocktail recipe, margarita recipe, tequila drink, cinco de mayo drink, summer cocktail, party recipes 
#cocktailrecipes #margaritatime #entertainingathome

Poolside Paloma 🧡

4-5 limes juiced (about 1/3 cup) 
Equal parts fresh grapefruit juice (about 1/3 cup) 
1 TBSP agave - or more to taste 
2 ounces silver tequila 
Sparkling water 
 
Mix first 4 ingredients in a shaker. Pour over ice about 3/4 full and top rest with sparkling water. Give it a stir and enjoy! 

#palomas #cocktailrecipes #cocktailtime #tequilatime #cincodemayo

Strawberry Basil Margarita 🍓🌱 

Super tasty and not too sweet! This makes 2 servings

And if you want to make it on the rocks use regular strawberries and muddle them really well with the basil and lime. Add tequila, agave and a little water. Shake and serve over ice. 

#margaritatime #margaritarecipe #cincodemayo2023

Getting my bedroom set up for success for Better Sleep Month with the Better Sleep Council! #ad 

Here’s how I set my bedroom up for sleep success:

First if you’ve been around lately you know I’ve been on a decluttering kick and one of the first places I started was my bedroom! Having a space that is clear of clutter helps you relax and keep your mind clear so you can focus on rest. This includes making your bed!

Another great way to set yourself up for success is to have the right environment for you! For us that’s light blocking window treatments and soft lighting for when you’re winding down for the day. But it could be cozy throw blankets and candles, whatever works best for you! 

And you can enter for the chance to win one of the prizes below by sharing your set up! Don’t forget to enter! 

● How to enter:
○ Follow @bettersleeporg on Instagram
○ Post your entry to your Instagram profile
○ In your post, use: #BSCcontest and #BetterSleepMonth
○ In your post, tag @bettersleeporg 
○ Instagram profiles must be public to enter
● Prizes:
○ The ‘organized’ winner : $400 to go toward new pillows and bedroom accessories
○ The ‘aesthetic’ winner: $600 to go toward new bedding and bedroom accessories
○ The ‘creative’ winner: $1,500 to go toward a bedroom remodel and one consultation (via Zoom) with a BSC spokeswoman to help advise on setting up your bedroom for ‘sleep success

My love for peonies goes decades back 🌸  they will forever be a favorite!!

If you want them to last as long as possible in your vase this is when to cut! 

If you cut once they are bloomed they will still look and smell amazing but for only a day or two. If you cut them too early then may not open. Just remember to check if they feel like a marshmallow 😁 

And if there’s ants just give the plant a shake before cutting 😉

Day 12! The final day of 12 Days of Christmas Decor 🥰🎄✨ I finished my mantle garland and decor and here’s some of my favorite tips. 
1. Add the second strand of lights! I never regret adding more lights (ok maybe don’t go crazy but you know what I mean 😆) and having two different style of lights will be ever better. 
2. Have a mixture of finishes and textures to keep things interesting and to create dimension. 
3. Think about function for you.. I cluster our stockings so we can use our fireplace easier and I like how it looks 😁 you style things any certain way if it doesn’t work for you. Thank you for sticking through this fun series with me!! 🫶🏻
